Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @sweet potato{2} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel!). Pop the wedges on a low sided wide #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with @oil{1%tbsp}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out. Set aside.

Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1} then halve lengthways. Thinly slice widthways. Quarter the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}. Pick the @mint{1}(leaves picked and roughly chopped, stalks discarded).

Once your oven is hot, roast the sweet potatoes on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the potatoes nicely spread out.

Meanwhile, peel the @garlic cloves{2} and pop into a square of #foil{} with a drizzle of @oil{1%tsp} and scrunch to enclose it. Pop it on the tray next to the wedges and roast until soft, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Pop the @falafel mix{150%g} into a #medium mixing bowl{} and add half the @zahtar{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and add the @water{150%ml}. Mix together until well combined then set aside for ~{3-4%minutes} (the mixture will thicken in this time).

Put the @Greek style natural yoghurt{150%g} in a #bowl{} and add the @water{1%tbsp} and the @olive oil{1.5%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and stir together well. Once the garlic is roasted, carefully open the parcel (it will be hot) mash the garlic with a #fork{}. Add the garlic and any oil to the yogurt. Stir to combine everything together then set aside.

Once the falafel mixture has thickened, shape into balls (4 per person) - pop them on a #plate{} as you make them.

> Wet your hands before shaping the falafels to prevent them from sticking to your hands.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large frying pan{} over medium high heat. Once hot, add the falafels and cook, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{3-4%minutes}. Pop onto a baking tray and bake on the top shelf of your oven until firm and cooked through, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Pop the @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{4} (2 per person) into your oven to warm through for the last 2-3 mins of potato cooking time. Once everything is ready, spread a spoonful of yoghurt dressing on the bottom of each wrap. Add a handful of lettuce to each followed by some tomatoes. Pop 2 falafel per wrap on top then drizzle on a little more yogurt. Sprinkle over the mint. Fold up and pop on your plates. Sprinkle the remaining zahtar on the sweet potato wedges and serve them alongside your wraps. Enjoy!